<content type="str">WESTERLY — Working as a substitute teacher would be ideal for Angel-Lena Smith, of Westerly, a certified paraprofessional who is studying part time for her teaching certificate. 
 
“I would like to get into the district to have my name known — the ideal schedule would be about three days a week,” she said. “It’s all about networking, so by the time I’m finished with school to be a teacher, that way I’d already be in the district.” 
 
Smith, 30, was among a steady stream of applicants who attended the school district’s Winter Open House at the Westerly High School cafeteria Saturday. The event served as a job fair for substitute positions as teachers, paraprofessionals, custodians, and bus drivers. 
   
